#10000
Entrance to the Verdant Depths~
The path west from the Forest of Confusion opens into a vast shadowed expanse where trees of impossible girth tower overhead, their @@Gbark black with age@@N and slicked with emerald moss.
The air grows thick and cloying, heavy with the scent of ancient loam and something older beneath it -- wet stone, deep root, the exhalation of centuries of patient growth.
Twin pillars of gnarled oak flank the trail southward, their roots woven together across the earth like clasped fingers forming an arch of living wood that seems to tighten the deeper one ventures.
The silence here is not the absence of sound but a presence in itself, pressing inward from the canopy with a weight that discourages voices and slows thought.
Whatever this forest was before it became what it is now, that earlier self is buried too deep to excavate; only the depth remains, and the darkness, and the certainty of being watched by something that has always been here.
