#10055
The Deepwood~
The forest changes here with a totality that precludes gradual adjustment; the trees are not merely large but architecturally alien, their trunks forming shapes that defy natural growth, their bark smooth and dark and warm to the touch.
The space between them has a quality of deliberate arrangement, as though the forest has been designed by an intelligence that considers human movement to be something to be guided rather than permitted.
The paths that exist here were not made by the passing of creatures but by the forest's own decision about where things should be allowed to move, and deviating from those paths encounters a resistance that is not quite physical but is absolutely real.
There is a subsonic presence in this place that distinguishes itself from the vibration of the old growth boundary by being oriented rather than ambient -- it comes from a specific direction, from below and to the south, from something that is both the forest and older than the forest.
Nothing that enters the Deepwood without purpose finds its way out again by accident; the forest does not permit accidental exits any more than it permits accidental entry.
~
