A thornfang whelp moves through the undergrowth of the predator's den, its size smaller than the adults but its behavior identical in every relevant way.

~
The thornfang whelp has not yet reached the full size of the pack's adults but has already been trained to the pack's hunting methodology; it is smaller, faster, and less experienced in absorbing damage, which makes it dangerous in different ways than the adults.

~
