rootbound guardian~
a rootbound guardian~
A rootbound guardian stands at the inner boundary of the Rootmother's domain, its body a dense framework of living roots shaped into a form that serves the function of a guardian without having been designed as one.

~
The rootbound guardian grew from the Rootmother's root-network in response to intrusion; each one is a temporary extension of her will given physical form, and when it is no longer needed it will simply reintegrate with the network it came from.

~
