canopy strangler~
a canopy strangler~
A canopy strangler descends from the canopy above, its vine-mass body uncoiling from a resting position in the branches to drop toward the forest floor.

~
The canopy strangler waits in the upper canopy for extended periods, its body perfectly still and its color matching the surrounding foliage; it has no need to hunt because it has learned that prey comes to it if it positions itself along a frequently-used path and waits.

~
