rotting stag~
a rotting stag~
A rotting stag moves through the undergrowth, its dead flesh held together by the fungal network that has colonized its body and the antlers still intact and functional despite everything else about it that is not.

~
The fungal infection that animated this stag did so long after the animal's death, working upward from the carcass through the root-network to introduce its animating chemistry; the result is a creature that behaves like the predator the original stag never was.

~
