thorn wasp swarm~
a thorn wasp swarm~
A thorn wasp swarm moves through the air as a shifting cloud of individually tiny but collectively dangerous organisms, their thorned limbs making the swarm's surface appear to bristle constantly.

~
The thorn wasp swarm has no individual intelligence but demonstrates collective behavior that serves its reproductive needs with the efficiency of a well-designed system; each individual acts on chemical signals from its neighbors, and the cloud as a whole responds to threats with the speed of a single organism.

~
