barkskin wolf~
a barkskin wolf~
A barkskin wolf moves through the undergrowth, its hide so thoroughly hardened by the forest's particular biology that it produces a faint sound like wood shifting when it moves quickly.

~
The barkskin wolf is a deepwood wolf variant whose hide has undergone a secondary transformation beyond the standard darkening; the bark-hardening is a defensive adaptation that the forest has been developing across multiple generations of this pack, and this individual represents the current state of that project.

~
