deepwood centipede~
a deepwood centipede~
A deepwood centipede moves through the undergrowth with the fluid, segmented efficiency of something whose locomotive system has been optimized over millions of years for exactly this terrain.

~
The deepwood centipede is venomous in all developmental stages, but the adult's venom has been augmented by the forest's chemistry to a potency substantially beyond what the species achieves on the surface; contact with the mandibles introduces a compound that is immediately and insistently uncomfortable.

~
