gloomwing moth~
a gloomwing moth~
A gloomwing moth moves through the shadows near the canopy, its wing-surface releasing a continuous fall of fine particles that catch what little light reaches this deep.

~
The gloomwing moth's wing-dust is its primary survival mechanism: a chemical compound produced by modified wing-scales that causes disorientation in the respiratory and navigational systems of most creatures that breathe it, creating the window of vulnerability the moth uses to feed.

~
