corpseflower lurker~
a corpseflower lurker~
A corpseflower lurker has positioned itself in a gap in the undergrowth, its broad petals spread wide and its scent -- which approximates the smell of a fresh carcass -- carrying through the immediate area.

~
The corpseflower lurker lures prey with a scent system that mimics the specific chemical signatures of decay; it has no ability to pursue prey that does not come to it, which means it has spent the entirety of its existence developing the most efficient lure possible, and the result is convincing enough to have worked on everything in this forest.

~
