a brambleback tortoise~
A brambleback tortoise moves through the undergrowth with the unhurried confidence of something whose defensive systems make speed irrelevant as a survival strategy.

~
The brambleback tortoise's shell has been colonized by thorn-producing plants to a depth that makes conventional attack inadvisable; the thorns are not a passive defense but an active one, extending toward contact and retracting for repositioning with a speed that the rest of the tortoise's behavior does not suggest it is capable of.

~
