deepwood prowler~
a deepwood prowler~
A deepwood prowler moves through the undergrowth, its large feline body held low and its gait producing no sound despite its size.

~
The deepwood prowler is the forest's most conventional predator in form and the least conventional in practice; it has learned from the forest's own intelligence that patience is more reliable than speed, and it applies that lesson with a rigor that makes it dangerous in the specific, technical way that expertise makes things dangerous.

~
