#10062
Blightwood Ancient~
the Blightwood Ancient~
The Blightwood Ancient is here, its form occupying the decay-throne at the center of the hollow -- ancient rotting mega-treant and ecology in one, the distinction between it and the decomposing environment it inhabits having ceased to be meaningful.

~
It has been here since before the forest was called the Verdant Depths, since before there was anyone to call it anything; it has watched everything that has entered its domain decompose, and it has the patience of something that knows, with absolute certainty, that everything decomposes eventually, and that eventually it will get to this too.

The spores that fall constantly from its mass carry the chemistry of centuries of accumulated decay; the air in the throne room is thick with them, and breathing here is already participating in the Ancient's process of converting everything into more of itself.

~
